A group of extremely wealthy people in late XIX century in America, consisting of, among others, Clay Frick, Jay Gould, Andrew Mellon, JP Morgan and John D. Rockefeller. They were known for ruthless exploitation of workers and corrupting officials so that they can build and maintain their monopoly empires (trusts) that controlled oil production, railroads, steel etc.

